“Even when someone rejects the message, missionaries need to learn to have a positive attitude, because the message is still true, whether accepted or not. Now I know that tracting isn't very efficient, but I think it is good for the soul of the missionaries.”  – James E. Faust, LDS Church News
“In order to do well, missionary work has to be totally positive.”  – James E. Faust, LDS Church News
